Police said the incident happened earlier on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - A security guard has been shot and killed at a shopping mall in Randburg. Police said the incident happened earlier on Tuesday at the Randridge Mall. Spokesperson Balan Muthan said six men entered a store and fled with cash and other items. “A security guard was shot dead in the lower abdomen and the suspects fled the scene in a blue Toyota Corolla and a Hyundai. These suspects are still at large." He said police were investigating a case of business robbery, armed robbery and murder. “The security guard was treated on the scene, but he passed away en route to the hospital.”